    /// Golden-master regression test for Movement.Step. Runs a fixed 300-tick scripted input
    /// sequence against FakeFlatGroundWorld and compares every tick's full state to a baseline
    /// recorded at v1.3 sign-off. Any drift in Movement.Step's behavior — state-machine ordering,
    /// timer math, integration constants, sweep order, edge-flag emission, anything observable in
    /// MovementState or EdgeFlags — surfaces here on the next CI push with a diff message pointing
    /// at the first divergent tick.
    ///
    /// MovementTests covers correctness per-mechanic with hand-written assertions; the golden master
    /// covers "does the full integrated trajectory still match what shipped at v1.3." The two
    /// catch different classes of bugs.
    ///
    /// Bootstrap workflow (one-time, at v1.3 sign-off):
    ///   1. BaselineCsv is empty → Trajectory_MatchesBaseline fails with the full CSV in the message.
    ///   2. Copy the CSV from the failure output, paste between the BaselineCsv `""`.
    ///   3. Re-run → passes. Commit the file.
    /// Intentional update (e.g. tuning pass):
    ///   1. Run the [Explicit] RegenerateBaseline test from Test Runner; copy output; paste into BaselineCsv.
    public class MovementGoldenMasterTests
    {
